text.tspan: Jesus my Shepherd in tenderness came
Assurance and Joy of Salvation — General
Like a fine woman, He swept and He searched,
For one lost coin which to Him had great worth;
When by His Spirit He shined on my sin,
All night was scattered, and He entered in!
Once, lost in sin, from my Father I roamed,
Yet deep within I still longed for a home;
But by His mercy this prodigal sees!
I was once dead, but now God lives in me!
Through the Son’s death, I have access to God,
Through the sweet washing of His precious blood;
One with the Triune God, living in me!
What love divine that my God has made known,
Sinners and the Triune God find a home!
What grace bestowed to the less than the least—
Oh, hallelujah! God’s living in me!
